	<http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> """PMID:2758466 (ES): The glp-1gene is smaller than lin-12 (see Figure 1) and is predicted to encode a smaller primary translation product (1295 
versus 1429 amino acids). Corresponding exons in the two genes average 
50% nucleotide sequence identity and require little gapping to optimize 
alignments. """^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> , """PMID:18700817 (ES): The LAG-2 and DSL-1 interactions with LIN-12 in the two-hybrid assay are consistent with previous genetic studies in
C. elegans and with biochemical analyses of Notch ligand/receptor
interactions in other systems. """^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/contributor> "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> ;
	<http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date> "2017-03-13"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .

